node.text: "Nope, I haven't seen the hamster anywhere" 😼🐾 Mia, our kitty who tested positive for FeLV five months ago, is doing phenomenal! After extensive research we decided to add Interferon to her treatment plan in addition to vitamins and a great diet. Oral Interferon therapy is regarded as "immunomodulatory", which helps to neutralize foreign bodies that try to attack the immune system. Although it's not widely practiced in traditional pet medicine the results we've seen in Mia make us so hopeful that she will continue to live a very happy and spoiled kitty life! 😻❤️ Have any of you tried Interferon therapy to treat any feline disease?? #adoptdontshop #rorytotherescue
